Title: Echinococcus alveolaris treated by right trisegmentectomy.
Abstract: A case of Echinococcus alveolaris of the liver treated by right trisegmentectomy is reported. The imaging procedures (sonography, CT, angiography) ensuring preoperative diagnosis were of help in performing of resections and they can also be used in the postoperative follow-up.
