Title: Posttraumatic unilateral blepharospasm treated by selective facial neurectomy.
Abstract: A patient who presented with posttraumatic ptosis of the right upper eyelid proved to be a case of unilateral blepharospasm with facial palsy of the forehead. He was successfully treated with selective facial neurectomy.
