Title: Sick sinus syndrome treated by ventricular inhibited pacemaker and radiofrequency programmed ventricular stimulation (author's transl).
Abstract: It is described a patient with sick sinus syndrome (atrial bradycardia and reciprocating junctional tachycardia) treated by a permanent ventricular inhibited pacemaker. The catheter is been also connected with a radiofrequency device implanted in order to interrupt the reciprocating tachyarrhythmia with programmed ventricular stimulation.
